{"title_page": "Luis Negr\u00f3n", "text_new": "{{short description|Puerto Rican writer}}\n{{Infobox writer\n| name = Luis Negr\u00f3n\n| birth_name = \n| image = \n| birth_date = 1970\n| birth_place = [[Guayama]], [[Puerto Rico]]\n| occupation = Writer\n| period = 2000s-present\n| nationality = [[Puerto Rico|Puerto Rican]]\n| notableworks = ''Mundo Cruel''\n| spouse = \n| website = \n}}\n\n'''Luis Negr\u00f3n''' (born 1970 in [[Guayama]], [[Puerto Rico]]) is a [[Puerto Rico|Puerto Rican]] writer.\n\nNegr\u00f3n originally studied journalism, which he said taught him how to write and gave him confidence.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.centerforfiction.org/magazine/interviews/luis-negron-interviewed-by-matt-nelson/|title=Luis Negr\u00f3n, interviewed by Matt Nelson|last=Nelson|first=Matt|date=2013|website=The Center for Fiction|access-date=April 8, 2019}}</ref> He lives in [[Santurce, San Juan, Puerto Rico|Santurce]], a barrio in [[San Juan, Puerto Rico|San Juan]], and works in a bookstore.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nHis debut [[short story]] collection, ''Mundo Cruel'', was published in 2010 and has seen five printings in [[Spanish language|Spanish]]. The stories in the book focus on [[gay]] life in Santurce.<ref>[http://www.dailytexanonline.com/life-and-arts/2013/03/18/luis-negron-keeps-mundo-cruel-brief-but-enjoyable \"Luis Negr\u00f3n keeps 'Mundo Cruel' brief, but enjoyable\"]. ''[[The Daily Texan]]'', March 18, 2013.</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lambdaliterary.org/reviews/03/05/mundo-cruel-by-luis-negron/|title='Mundo Cruel' by Luis Negr\u00f3n|last=Lopez|first=Dan|date=2013-03-06|website=Lambda Literary|access-date=2019-04-08}}</ref> An English translation by [[Suzanne Jill Levine]] was published by [[Seven Stories Press]] in 2013,<ref>[[Bruce Benderson]], [http://www.out.com/entertainment/art-books/2013/02/18/mundo-cruel-luis-negron \"The Queen of Satire\"]. ''[[Out (magazine)|Out]]'', February 18, 2013.</ref> and won the [[Lambda Literary Award for Gay Fiction]] at the [[26th Lambda Literary Awards]] in 2014.<ref>[https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/style-blog/wp/2014/06/02/lambda-literary-awards/ \"Lambda Awards honor best lesbian, gay, bisexual and transgender books\"]. ''[[Washington Post]]'', June 2, 2014.</ref>\n\nHe was also coeditor, with David Caleb Acevedo and Mois\u00e9s Agosto, of ''Los otros cuerpos'', an [[anthology]] of writing by [[LGBT]] Puerto Ricans.<ref>[http://www.nydailynews.com/latino/puerto-rican-lit-coming-tonight-new-york-article-1.298550 \"Puerto Rican lit coming out tonight in New York\"]. ''[[New York Daily News]]'', June 25, 2008.</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.indentagency.com/luis-negron|title=Luis Negr\u00f3n|website=Indent Literary Agency|language=en-US|access-date=2019-04-08}}</ref> As of 2014, Negr\u00f3n was working a novel, memoir, and play.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n== Influences ==\nNegr\u00f3n has claimed [[Filmmaking|filmmakers]] [[Rainer Werner Fassbinder|R. W. Fassbinder]] and [[John Waters]] as influences, as well as French writer [[Jean Genet]] and Argentinean author [[Manuel Puig]].<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.asymptotejournal.com/blog/2014/07/03/interview-with-luis-negron/|title=Interview with Luis Negr\u00f3n|last=Richter|first=Eva|date=July 3, 2014|website=Asymptote|access-date=April 8, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Works==\n*''Los otros cuerpos: Antolog\u00eda de tem\u00e1tica gay, l\u00e9sbica y queer desde Puerto Rico y su di\u00e1spora''. (2007, {{ISBN|0-9773612-8-4}})\n*''Mundo Cruel'' (2010, {{ISBN|978-1596087798}})\n*''Mundo Cruel'', English translation (2013, {{ISBN|978-1609804183}}) <ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sevenstories.com/books/3328-mundo-cruel |title=Mundo Cruel: Stories |publisher=Seven Stories Press}}</ref>\n*''Los Tres Golpes,'' (2016, {{ISBN|978-0865817081}})<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://revistacruce.com/letras/item/2502-los-tres-golpes-de-luis-negron-solidaridad-amor-y-carencia|title=Cruce - 'Los tres golpes' de Luis Negr\u00f3n: solidaridad, amor y carencia|last=V\u00e9lez|first=Alexandra Pag\u00e1n|website=revistacruce.com|language=es-es|access-date=2019-04-08}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Negron, Luis}}\n[[Category:1970 births]]\n[[Category:Puerto Rican male short story writers]]\n[[Category:Puerto Rican short story writers]]\n[[Category:Puerto Rican male writers]]\n[[Category:LGBT writers from Puerto Rico]]\n[[Category:Gay writers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Guayama, Puerto Rico]]\n[[Category:People from Santurce, Puerto Rico]]\n[[Category:Lambda Literary Award for Gay Fiction winners]]\n[[Category:Spanish-language LGBT writers]]\n\n\n{{PuertoRico-bio-stub}}\n{{lgbt-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Puerto Rican writer}}\n{{Infobox writer\n| name = Luis Negr\u00f3n\n| birth_name = \n| image = \n| birth_date = 1970\n| birth_place = [[Guayama]], [[Puerto Rico]]\n| occupation = Writer\n| period = 2000s-present\n| nationality = [[Puerto Rico|Puerto Rican]]\n| notableworks = ''Mundo Cruel''\n| spouse = \n| website = \n}}\n\n'''Luis Negr\u00f3n''' (born 1970 in [[Guayama]], [[Puerto Rico]]) is a [[Puerto Rico|Puerto Rican]] writer. \n\nNegr\u00f3n originally studied journalism, which he said taught him how to write and gave him confidence.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.centerforfiction.org/magazine/interviews/luis-negron-interviewed-by-matt-nelson/|title=Luis Negr\u00f3n, interviewed by Matt Nelson|last=Nelson|first=Matt|date=2013|website=The Center for Fiction|access-date=April 8, 2019}}</ref> He lives in [[Santurce, San Juan, Puerto Rico|Santurce]], a barrio in [[San Juan, Puerto Rico|San Juan]], and works in a bookstore.<ref name=\":0\" /> \n\nHis debut [[short story]] collection, ''Mundo Cruel'', was published in 2010 and has seen five printings in [[Spanish language|Spanish]]. The stories in the book focus on [[gay]] life in Santurce.<ref>[http://www.dailytexanonline.com/life-and-arts/2013/03/18/luis-negron-keeps-mundo-cruel-brief-but-enjoyable \"Luis Negr\u00f3n keeps 'Mundo Cruel' brief, but enjoyable\"]. ''[[The Daily Texan]]'', March 18, 2013.</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lambdaliterary.org/reviews/03/05/mundo-cruel-by-luis-negron/|title='Mundo Cruel' by Luis Negr\u00f3n|last=Lopez|first=Dan|date=2013-03-06|website=Lambda Literary|access-date=2019-04-08}}</ref> An English translation by [[Suzanne Jill Levine]] was published by [[Seven Stories Press]] in 2013,<ref>[[Bruce Benderson]], [http://www.out.com/entertainment/art-books/2013/02/18/mundo-cruel-luis-negron \"The Queen of Satire\"]. ''[[Out (magazine)|Out]]'', February 18, 2013.</ref> and won the [[Lambda Literary Award for Gay Fiction]] at the [[26th Lambda Literary Awards]] in 2014.<ref>[https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/style-blog/wp/2014/06/02/lambda-literary-awards/ \"Lambda Awards honor best lesbian, gay, bisexual and transgender books\"]. ''[[Washington Post]]'', June 2, 2014.</ref>\n\nHe was also coeditor, with David Caleb Acevedo and Mois\u00e9s Agosto, of ''Los otros cuerpos'', an [[anthology]] of writing by [[LGBT]] Puerto Ricans.<ref>[http://www.nydailynews.com/latino/puerto-rican-lit-coming-tonight-new-york-article-1.298550 \"Puerto Rican lit coming out tonight in New York\"]. ''[[New York Daily News]]'', June 25, 2008.</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.indentagency.com/luis-negron|title=Luis Negr\u00f3n|website=Indent Literary Agency|language=en-US|access-date=2019-04-08}}</ref> As of 2014, Negr\u00f3n was working a novel, memoir, and play.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n== Influences ==\nNegr\u00f3n has claimed [[Filmmaking|filmmakers]] [[Rainer Werner Fassbinder|R. W. Fassbinder]] and [[John Waters]] as influences, as well as French writer [[Jean Genet]] and Argentinean author [[Manuel Puig]].<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.asymptotejournal.com/blog/2014/07/03/interview-with-luis-negron/|title=Interview with Luis Negr\u00f3n|last=Richter|first=Eva|date=July 3, 2014|website=Asymptote|access-date=April 8, 2019}}</ref> \n\n==Works==\n*''Los otros cuerpos: Antolog\u00eda de tem\u00e1tica gay, l\u00e9sbica y queer desde Puerto Rico y su di\u00e1spora''. (2007, {{ISBN|0-9773612-8-4}})\n*''Mundo Cruel'' (2010, {{ISBN|978-1596087798}})\n*''Mundo Cruel'', English translation (2013, {{ISBN|978-1609804183}}) <ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sevenstories.com/books/3328-mundo-cruel |title=Mundo Cruel: Stories |publisher=Seven Stories Press}}</ref>\n*''Los Tres Golpes,'' (2016, {{ISBN|978-0865817081}})<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://revistacruce.com/letras/item/2502-los-tres-golpes-de-luis-negron-solidaridad-amor-y-carencia|title=Cruce - 'Los tres golpes' de Luis Negr\u00f3n: solidaridad, amor y carencia|last=V\u00e9lez|first=Alexandra Pag\u00e1n|website=revistacruce.com|language=es-es|access-date=2019-04-08}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Negron, Luis}}\n[[Category:1970 births]]\n[[Category:Puerto Rican male short story writers]]\n[[Category:Puerto Rican short story writers]]\n[[Category:Puerto Rican male writers]]\n[[Category:LGBT writers from Puerto Rico]]\n[[Category:Gay writers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Guayama, Puerto Rico]]\n[[Category:People from Santurce, Puerto Rico]]\n[[Category:Lambda Literary Award for Gay Fiction winners]]\n\n\n{{PuertoRico-bio-stub}}\n{{lgbt-bio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Bearcat", "label": "safe", "comment": "add category", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Luis_Negr%C3%B3n"}
